        list - A List of HashMaps as a holder for holding results from Firestore
        username - username to be found, can be null
        IdentifierField - A option check device id specifically, will look for Identifier (e.g. username) if null
        返回:

        抛出:

        public void setupPlayer​(java.lang.String username,
                        @Nullable
                        java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> qrInventory,
                        @Nullable
                        java.util.HashMap contact,
                        @Nullable
                        java.lang.Integer qrCount,
                        @Nullable
                        java.lang.Integer totalScore,
                        @Nullable
                        java.lang.Integer highestUnique,
                        java.lang.Boolean owner,
                        java.lang.String id)
        Load current Player class locally
        参数:
        username - is guaranteed to be unique, it notifies Observer once player is created
        qrInventory - a ArrayList object store player's qr code(s)
        contact - player's contact info
        qrCount - player's qrcount number
        totalScore - player's Score so far
        highestUnique - player's higest score for unique qrcode
        owner - A boolean whether this player is an owner
        id - A String for DeviceId

        public void saveOtherPlayerData​(java.lang.Integer qrCount,
                                java.lang.Integer totalScore,
                                java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> qrInventory,
                                java.util.HashMap contact,
                                java.lang.Integer highestUnique,
                                java.lang.String id,
                                java.lang.Boolean owner,
                                java.lang.String identifier,
                                java.lang.Boolean overwrite)
                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Save other player's data on Firestore
        参数:
        qrCount - player's qrCount
        totalScore - player's total score
        qrInventory - player's qrInventory
        contact - player's contact info
        highestUnique - player's highest unique score
        id - player's deviceID
        owner - if player is an owner or not
        identifier - player's username
        overwrite - whether overwrites player's data
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - wrong collection name is going to throw exception

      • savePlayerData

        public void savePlayerData​(@Nullable
                           java.lang.Integer qrCount,
                           @Nullable
                           java.lang.Integer totalScore,
                           @Nullable
                           java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> qrInventory,
                           @Nullable
                           java.util.HashMap contact,
                           @Nullable
                           java.lang.Integer highestUnique,
                           @Nullable
                           java.lang.String id,
                           @Nullable
                           java.lang.Boolean owner,
                           java.lang.Boolean addIdentifier)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Update/Create a player's data based on the addIdentifier boolean flag
        参数:
        qrCount - player's qrCount
        totalScore - player's total Score
        qrInventory - an Arraylist of qrHashes
        contact - contact info for player
        highestUnique - highest score from a unique qrcode
        id - DeviceId of the given user
        owner - a Boolean variable indicates if this is an owner
        addIdentifier - if true create a new player in database, update a user otherwise
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - if collection is invalid
